---
import PitchLayout from '../../layouts/PitchLayout.astro';
---

<PitchLayout slug="origin">
  <h1 class="slide-headline">But getting here wasn't easy. We had to spend months on data before our first&nbsp;trade.</h1>

  <p class="slide-body-small" style="margin-bottom: 32px; color: var(--text-muted);">Every dev, quant, and agent hits the same wall. The infrastructure doesn't exist yet. You have to clean up data, build your own backtesting engine and execution from&nbsp;scratch.</p>

  <div class="cards-row">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">{'{ }'}</div>
      <p class="card-label">Market data is fragmented</p>
      <p class="slide-body-small">Kalshi and Polymarket use different schemas. Neither stores order book history. You normalize them yourself and capture order book data in real time, forever.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">~/</div>
      <p class="card-label">Source data isn't for trading</p>
      <p class="slide-body-small">Weather lives in GRIB files, macro in PDFs, sports across a dozen APIs. None map to contract resolution windows. You write the joins yourself, per vertical.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">$$$</div>
      <p class="card-label">Agents pay for it twice</p>
      <p class="slide-body-small">10+ API calls to reason about one contract. Bloated JSON the model didn't ask for. Every call is tokens, every token is money. By the time context is assembled, the market moved.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PitchLayout>
